Reasoning: The paper presents a probabilistic model for learning and inference of continuous-time physiological processes using electronic health record data. This involves developing a novel algorithm for handling irregularly sampled, temporally correlated, and informatively censored data. The paper also demonstrates the diagnostic and prognostic utility of the model in a critical care prognosis setting. Given these aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also involves aspects of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) in terms of handling sensitive health data and analyzing patient state transitions.
